A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO HOMELESS YOUTH.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Act 130, Session Laws of Hawaii 2022 (Act 130),
2 established a safe spaces for youth pilot program within the
3 department of human services. Act 130 will be repealed on June
4 30, 2025. The office of youth services has worked on planning
5 and developing the safe spaces for youth pilot program and, with
6 appropriations, recommends the pilot program become permanent,
7 and is ready to open the first state-funded shelter for young
8 adults on the island of Hawaii.
9 The purpose of this Act is to:
10 (1) Make the safe spaces for youth pilot program a
11 permanent program within the office of youth services;
12 and
13 (2) Provide funding for a permanent safe spaces for youth
14 program in the office of youth services.
15 SECTION 2. Chapter 352D, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
16 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
17 and to read as follows:
