1 "§352D- Safe spaces for youth program; establishment;
2 reports. (a) There is established within the office of youth
3 services a safe spaces for youth program, which shall provide,
4 subject to the availability of funds, safe spaces in each county
5 for youth and young adults experiencing homelessness or at risk
6 of homelessness.
7 (b) The program shall collaborate with all departments of
8 the State and its political subdivisions that offer services for
9 the purpose of ensuring the well-being of youth and young adults
10 in Hawaii, including the department of education, department of
11 corrections and rehabilitation, department of health, department
12 of human services, department of land and natural resources,
13 department of law enforcement, state office on homelessness and
14 housing solutions, county police departments and other agencies,
15 and judiciary, to coordinate the identification of youth and
16 young adults who are experiencing homelessness, and placement of
17 these youth and young adults at a shelter for homeless youth or
18 young adults.
19 (c) The office of youth services may enter into contracts
20 with nonprofit organizations to provide services for youth or
21 young adults experiencing homelessness or who are at risk of
