2 subsection shall have the knowledge, experience, and
3 qualifications, including licenses as needed for child caring
4 institutions, and other requirements to operate a shelter for
5 homeless youth or young adults experiencing homelessness or at
6 risk of homelessness. Youth under the age of eighteen shall not
7 be sheltered with young adults age eighteen to twenty-four.
8 (d) Notwithstanding any other law to the contrary, a
9 shelter for homeless youth or young adults contracted under
10 subsection (c) may admit a youth into the shelter's care for up
11 to ninety days without the consent of the youth's parent or
12 guardian.
13 (e) The office shall submit a report pertaining to the
14 safe spaces for youth program to the legislature no later than
15 twenty days prior to the convening of each regular session.
16 (f) The office may adopt rules pursuant to chapter 91
17 necessary to carry out the purposes of this section.
18 (g) For the purposes of this section, "shelter for
19 homeless youth or young adults" means a facility that operates
20 to receive youth or young adults twenty-four hours a day, seven
